==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fusarole
<hw>Fu"sa*role</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>fusarolle</ets>, fr. It. <ets>fusaruolo</ets>, fr. <ets>fuso</ets>
spindle, shaft of a column. See <er>Fusee</er> a conical wheel.]</ety>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A molding generally placed under the echinus or
quarter round of capitals in the Doric, Ionic, and Corinthian orders of
architecture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fuscation</ent>⟦br⟧
